(firstQuint)Operative Plate Fixation Versus Replacement for Mason Type III Fracture of Radial Head.

 From April 2015 to October 2016, patients with comminuted radial head fractures diagnosed as Mason type III are retrospectively included in this study, they were treated with either operative plate or radial head replacement.

 All the patients are regularly followed up in clinic.

 Then we will compare the union rate and clinical functional outcome(Mayo score) between the 2 groups at 1 year after surgery.

